commit 1013ed5788202d91616c6f52a4e90d29c3809801
Author: Nexus-Digital-Automations <founder1@nexusdigitalautomations.com>
Date:   Tue May 5 11:16:10 2026 -0500

    Switch repo-index cache key from commit hash to tree hash
    
    git rev-parse HEAD^{tree} is stable across --amend, rebase, and reword
    operations — anything that changes commit metadata without touching files.
    The old commit-hash key would bust the cache and trigger a full rebuild on
    every such operation even though the index was still valid.
    
    Changes: rename get_head_sha → get_head_tree_sha (both GitPython and
    subprocess paths), rename LoadedIndex.commit_hash → tree_hash and
    _loaded_commit_hash → _loaded_tree_hash. IndexManifest.commit_hash
    and embedder parameter names left as-is (internal/on-disk, no benefit
    to renaming). Existing .context/ files keyed on old commit hashes will
    trigger one rebuild on next run, then stay hot.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

